    "description": "An interface surface freezes a Stable (or LTS) version window only when its freeze packet is within its freshness SLO, any waiver it relies on is unexpired, its deprecation packet is complete with no overdue removal, its surface-level version evidence is complete, an owner has signed off, and the public claim it backs is itself at or above the cutline. A surface that loses any of those freezes a label below the cutline (beta, preview, withdrawn) and never inherits an adjacent surface's frozen label."
  },
